ical Support.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Why There Is No Host-Only Mode","level":3,"anchor":"Why-There-Is-No-Host-Only-Mode"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework provides three network","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"attachment types: "},{"code":"VZNATNetworkDeviceAttachment","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"VZBridgedNetworkDeviceAttachment","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". None of these","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implements host-only semantics directly.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A host-only mode would require a user-space virtual network","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"switch built on top of ","type":"text"},{"code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"handling raw Ethernet frames, DHCP, and packet routing — a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"substantial subsystem that would need its own lifecycle","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"management and security hardening. Rather than ship a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"half-baked implementation or silently fall back to NAT","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(which would give VMs unintended internet access), this enum","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"only exposes modes that the Virtualization framework supports","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"natively.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need isolated host-guest communication, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","isActi